# Backend Structure

## Project Name
UCAB – Cab Booking System

## Objective

The backend structure of the UCAB application is developed using Node.js, Express.js, MongoDB, and Mongoose. The backend follows the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture to ensure scalability, maintainability, and organized code management.

---

## Technologies Used

- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB
- Mongoose
- JWT Authentication
- bcryptjs

---

## Backend Folder Structure

Server
│
├── server.js
│
├── config
│   └── db.js
│
├── models
│   ├── UserModel.js
│   ├── DriverModel.js
│   ├── RideModel.js
│   └── PaymentModel.js
│
├── controllers
│   ├── UserController.js
│   ├── DriverController.js
│   ├── RideController.js
│   └── PaymentController.js
│
├── routes
│   ├── userRoutes.js
│   ├── driverRoutes.js
│   ├── rideRoutes.js
│   └── paymentRoutes.js
│
├── middleware
│   └── authMiddleware.js
│
└── package.json

---

## Folder Description

### server.js
Main entry point of the application.

### config
Stores database configuration files.

### models
Contains MongoDB schemas and models.

### controllers
Contains business logic and request handling.

### routes
Defines API endpoints.

### middleware
Handles authentication and authorization.

---

## Backend Workflow

1. Client sends request.
2. Route receives request.
3. Controller processes request.
4. Model interacts with database.
5. Response is sent back to client.

---

## Benefits

- Modular architecture
- Easy maintenance
- Better scalability
- Organized code structure
- Secure authentication

---

## Outcome

Successfully designed the backend structure for the UCAB Cab Booking System using MVC architecture and MongoDB integration.

Project: UCAB Cab Booking System

